1. Introduction
1.1 Purpose
The purpose of this document is to define the functional and non-functional requirements for the Marketplace Web Application. This application will provide a platform for users to list items for sale, browse and purchase items, and provide feedback via reviews.

1.2 Scope
The application will be a web-based platform accessible via standard desktop and mobile browsers. Key features include user registration, item listing management, search and filtering, secure payment processing integration, and a product review/rating system.

1.3 Target Audience
Sellers: Individuals or small businesses looking to list products for sale.
Buyers: Users looking to browse, search, and purchase items.
Administrators: Personnel responsible for site maintenance, user moderation, and dispute resolution.

1.4 Acronyms
P1-P5: Priority in the increasing order. P1 has highest priority and P5 has least priority.

2. Functional Requirements
These define the specific actions the system must perform.

2.1 User Management (Authentication & Authorization)
FR-UM-01-	User Registration:	Users must be able to sign up using an email address, username, and password. (P1)
FR-UM-02-	User Login/Logout:	Users must be able to securely log in and out of the application. (P1)
FR-UM-03-	Profile Management:	Users must be able to view and edit their profile details (e.g., name, shipping address, payment methods). (P1)

2.2 Selling Functionaity (Seller)
FR-SELL-01-	Create Item Listing:	Sellers must be able to create a new product listing, including title, description, price, category, inventory quantity, and at least one image. (P1)
FR-SELL-02-	Manage Listings:	Sellers must be able to view, edit, and delete their active and inactive item listings. (P2)
FR-SELL-03-	Order Notification:	Sellers must receive a notification (email/in-app) when one of their items is purchased. (P5)
FR-SELL-04-	Order Status Update:	Sellers must be able to update the status of an order (e.g., "Pending," "Shipped," "Delivered"). (P3)

2.3 Buying Functionality (Buyer)
FR-BUY-01-	Item Search:	Buyers must be able to search for items by keywords in the title and description. (P1)
FR-BUY-02-	Item Filtering:	Buyers must be able to filter search results by criteria such as category, price range, and seller rating. (P2)
FR-BUY-03-	Shopping Cart:	Buyers must be able to add and remove items from a persistent shopping cart. (P4)
FR-BUY-04-	Checkout Process:	Buyers must be able to complete a purchase, providing shipping details and selecting a saved payment method. (P1)
FR-BUY-05-	Order History:	Buyers must be able to view a history of all their past and current orders, including tracking information if provided by the seller. (P3)

2.4 Review Functionality
FR-REV-01-	Post Product Review:	Buyers must be able to leave a review (text comment) and a rating (1-5 stars) for an item they have purchased. (P1)
FR-REV-02-	View Reviews:	All users must be able to view the aggregated rating and individual reviews on an item's product page. (P1)
FR-REV-03-	Seller Rating:	The system must calculate and display an average rating for each seller based on the reviews received on their sold items. (P3)

3. Non-Functional Requirements
These define the quality attributes of the system.

3.1 Security
NFR-SEC-01: All user passwords must be securely hashed. (P2)

3.2 Usability
NFR-US-01: The application must be fully responsive, providing a consistent and functional experience across desktop, tablet, and mobile devices. (P4)
NFR-US-02: All user flows (e.g., registration, checkout, listing creation) must be intuitive and require a maximum of three major steps. (P3)
NFR-US-03: All errors and system messages must be clear, non-technical, and provide actionable feedback to the user. (P2)

3.3 Technology Stack
Frontend:	React
Backend:	FastAPI
Database:	MongoDB
Hosting:	(not hosted)

4. Data Model Summary
The primary entities in the system will include:
User: Contains roles (Buyer/Seller/Admin), contact details, and authentication information.
Product: Contains details like name, description, price, quantity, category, and a foreign key to the Seller (User).
Order: Contains the list of products purchased, total price, shipping address, and foreign keys to the Buyer and Seller.
Review: Contains the rating, text comment, and foreign keys to the Buyer and the Product.
Category: Hierarchical list of categories for product classification.

Glossary:
Database: Storage system where data is stored.
React: A framework to create user interface applications.
FastAPI: A framework to create backend or logic of an application. It helps in exposing endpoints that frontend will use. 
